---
By: Ralph W. Trine
Locus:
  Page: 213
  Verse: 13
Tags:
  - Grief
---
The loss of friends by the transition we call death will not cause sorrow
to the soul that has come into the higher realization, for he knows there
is no such thing as death, for each of us is not only a partaker, but an
eternal partaker, of this Infinite Life.
